RetiOS is a Reticulum client for Apple platforms. It builds on Swift ports of
Mark Qvist's Reticulum ecosystem:

  Reticulum — https://github.com/markqvist/Reticulum
  LXMF       — https://github.com/markqvist/LXMF
  LXST       — https://github.com/markqvist/LXST
  NomadNet   — https://github.com/markqvist/NomadNet

via the ReticulumSwift, LXMFSwift, LXSTSwift, and NomadNetSwift packages. Those
packages bundle additional third-party components (i2pd, codec2, opus); see each
package's NOTICE / THIRD-PARTY documentation for their licenses.

Third-party components linked into the app (source code incorporated):

  Runestone 0.5.2 — https://github.com/simonbs/Runestone
    MIT License. Copyright (c) 2021 Simon Støvring.
    Runestone is the code-editor surface behind the Micron page editor
    (RetiOS/NomadNet/MicronSourceEditor.swift). It is UIKit-only, so it is
    linked for iOS/iPadOS destinations only (XcodeGen `destinationFilters:
    [iOS]`); the macOS build of RetiOS contains no Runestone code.

  tree-sitter 0.20.9 — https://github.com/tree-sitter/tree-sitter
    MIT License. Copyright (c) 2018-2023 Max Brunsfeld.
    A dependency of Runestone, pulled in transitively and therefore subject
    to the same iOS-only linkage.

